definitions.definition: in the direction of contraction of a muscle. ( E.g. extension of the lower arm via the elbow joint while contracting the triceps and other elbow extensor muscles; closing of the jaw while flexing the masseter ).

secondary_definitions: ( physiology ) (of a motion) in the direction of contraction of a muscle. ( E.g. extension of the lower arm via the elbow joint while contracting the triceps and other elbow extensor muscles; closing of the jaw while flexing the masseter ).
